e ability to communicate with the weather, interpretation of dreams, astral projection, and travel to upper and lower worlds.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1419";s:5:"count";s:2:"20";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"17";}i:134;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1486";s:4:"name";s:7:"Shiatsu";s:4:"slug";s:7:"shiatsu";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1486";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:342:"Shiatsu originated in Japan from traditional Chinese medicine.Shiatsu means ‚Äòfinger pressure‚Äô where a practitioner uses touch, comfortable pressure and manipulative techniques to adjust the body‚Äôs physical structure and balance its energy flow. It is a deeply relaxing experience and regular treatments can alleviate stress and illness.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1485";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"1";}i:135;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1452";s:4:"name";s:13:"Sound Healing";s:4:"slug";s:13:"sound-healing";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1452";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:314:"The universe is made up of sound waves that vibrate at different frequencies. Frequencies that vibrate at certain levels resonate deeply within the body. Sound healing, uses a combination of different instruments and tools to recreate certain frequencies that can deeply relax the mind and body triggering healing.";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:2:"12";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"2";}i:136;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1562";s:4:"name";s:20:"Spiritual Counseling";s:4:"slug";s:19:"spiritual-counselor";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1562";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:465:"A Spiritual Counselor helps the patient to deal with pain, grief,trauma and major difficult decisions keeping the patient‚Äôs spiritual growth in mind.The counselor combines spirituality with science while dealing with the client‚Äôs problems. By means of this process, the individual quietens the thoughts that are disturbing, finds an alternate way of looking at a situation, gets power from within, and gets the courage to face a problem rather than react to it.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1557";s:5:"count";s:3:"131";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"61";}i:137;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1521";s:4:"name";s:16:"Stress Reduction";s:4:"slug";s:16:"stress-reduction";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1521";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1502";s:5:"count";s:2:"14";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"6";}i:138;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1450";s:4:"name";s:18:"Subliminal Therapy";s:4:"slug";s:18:"subliminal-therapy";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1450";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:431:"Subliminal Therapy is a form of hypnosis where audio-subliminal messages are used to access the subconscious mind of the listener. Old, negative thought-patterns are disrupted and new, healthier thought-processes are introduced to the mind. Subliminal therapy music programs use therapeutic subliminal messages to access the subconscious mind and alter negative thought patterns in order to form a happier and healthier individual.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1447";s:5:"count";s:1:"4";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"4";}i:139;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1538";s:4:"name";s:15:"Sudarshan Kriya";s:4:"slug";s:15:"sudarshan-kriya";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1538";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:353:"Sudarshan Kriya is a unique, powerful technique of breathing in a rhythmic pattern. These breathing techniques bring one completely into the present moment, harmonizing mind, body and emotions. It aids in eliminating stress, fatigue and negative emotions such as anger, frustration and depression leaving one calm yet energized, focused and yet relaxed.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1535";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"1";}i:140;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1441";s:4:"name";s:13:"Sufi Whirling";s:4:"slug";s:13:"sufi-whirling";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1441";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:342:"Sufi Whirling is a form of Sama or physically active meditation which originated among Sufis. It emphasizes expressing universal love, peace and a mystical union with the divine through the dancing of whirling dervishes. The spinning and whirling has significance in the expression of energies experienced through this form of self-discovery.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1438";s:5:"count";s:1:"6";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"1";}i:141;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1397";s:4:"name";s:13:"Sujok Therapy";s:4:"slug";s:13:"sujok-therapy";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1397";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:533:"Sujok Therapy originated in Onnuri Medicine and is a system of treatment comprising of techniques that prevent and cure illnesses and restore health without any drugs. The basis of Sujok Therapy healing is the discovery of self-regulation of the energy system of the human body whereby each hand, foot and other locations are connected to and carry information of each organ. The hands and feet structurally correspond to micro points that can be used most effectively as remote controls to treat any diseased organ/part of the body.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1391";s:5:"count";s:2:"13";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"13";}i:142;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1545";s:4:"name";s:12:"Switch Words";s:4:"slug";s:12:"switch-words";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1545";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:370:"Switch Words are words that have the ability to switch your energy from one dimension to another. All words contain the power to be switch-words as they get registered in the sub-conscious part of the mind, so that one can even learn to use places, people and things to help them switch from one plane to another. This can become a valuable tool for self-transformation.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1391";s:5:"count";s:1:"5";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"5";}i:143;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1480";s:4:"name";s:7:"Tai Chi";s:4:"slug";s:7:"tai-chi";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1480";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:469:"Tai Chi is an ancient Chinese tradition that is practiced as a graceful form of mindful exercise to stimulate the movement of Chi in the energy system. It involves a series of movements performed in a slow, meditative manner and accompanied by deep breathing. Also called Tai Chi Chuan, it is a non-competitive, self-paced system of gentle physical exercise and stretching. Each posture flows into the next without a pause, ensuring that the body is in constant motion.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1475";s:5:"count";s:1:"7";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"3";}i:144;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1421";s:4:"name";s:18:"Tarot Card Reading";s:4:"slug";s:18:"tarot-card-reading";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1421";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:472:"In Tarot Card Reading, the therapist uses a pack of picture cards for the individual to choose from.By this method the Tarot Card Reader is able to connect with the present moment to tap into the inner source of all beings. The Reader studies the combination of cards picked by the individual and interprets the messages through their knowledge of symbolism and intuition. This guidance is the language of the Universe with specific relevance to the life of an individual.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1419";s:5:"count";s:3:"126";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:3:"115";}i:145;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1488";s:4:"name";s:12:"Thai Massage";s:4:"slug";s:12:"thai-massage";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1488";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:411:"Thai Massage (Nuad Bo-Rarn) is a mixture of Acupressure, Yoga and Zen Shiatsu which is inspired by the Buddhist teachings of energy flow. It applies pressure on various body parts by the practitioner using the palms of the hands, thumbs, elbows, and feet without the use of oil or lotion. Thai Massage offers deep relaxation, reduction in stress levels, improved overall circulation and increased energy levels.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1485";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"1";}i:146;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1394";s:4:"name";s:13:"Theta Healing";s:4:"slug";s:13:"theta-healing";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1394";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:508:"Theta Healing occurs in a deep meditative state that generates theta brain waves. These theta brain wave states are used to establish a strong connection with the soul on a higher vibrational level to facilitate healing. With this discovery, using the concept of seven planes of existence, one can connect to the Creator of All That Is. One can view the limiting beliefs from a higher perspective, replace them with changed positive beliefs and thereby, see miraculous healings for oneself as well as others.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1391";s:5:"count";s:2:"22";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"22";}i:147;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1453";s:4:"name";s:12:"Tibetan Bowl";s:4:"slug";s:12:"tibetan-bowl";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1453";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:463:"According to the Tibetan oral tradition, the existence of Tibetan singing bowls dates back to the time of the historical Buddha Shakyamuni (560 ‚Äì 480 B.C.). These bowls produce sounds and vibrations which invoke a deep state of relaxation which thereby naturally assists one in entering into meditation, with the ultimate goal of enlightenment. These are also used for deep relaxation, stress reduction, holistic healing, along with Reiki, and Chakra balancing.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1452";s:5:"count";s:2:"27";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"25";}i:148;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1417";s:4:"name";s:12:"Tibetan Yoga";s:4:"slug";s:12:"tibetan-yoga";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1417";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:447:"Tibetan Yoga is a Chinese method of controlling your internal energy which is called Qi. Tibetan Yoga is about the movement of the body while using the mind and synchronizing it with breath. It is basically the practice of synchronizing mind, body and breath to create the desired results. Tibetan Yoga gives the practitioner a strong and flexible body, purified energy meridians and clarity of thought through visualisation and mastery of breath.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1410";s:5:"count";s:1:"6";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"3";}i:149;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1530";s:4:"name";s:10:"Time Waver";s:4:"slug";s:10:"time-waver";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1530";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:419:"TimeWaver uses the possibilities of Information Field technology in the shape of high-class medical devices. They can explore the background and correlations of various diseases found in the information field, and then positively influence them in that very same information field. Moreover, the power of minimal electrical currents and frequencies can be used with an aim to directly treat the cells and physical body.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1527";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"1";}i:150;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1549";s:4:"name";s:22:"Transactional Analysis";s:4:"slug";s:22:"transactional-analysis";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1549";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:455:"Transactional Analysis is a theory developed by the Psychotherapist Eric Berne who defined the unit for human social interaction as ‚Äòtransaction‚Äô. When two or more people interact and communicate, verbally or nonverbally, it can offer suggestions and interventions to therapists. This can enable one to change and grow. Transactional Analysis is underpinned by the philosophy that people exist in various states of being that are mutually interactive.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1391";s:5:"count";s:1:"4";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"4";}i:151;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1403";s:4:"name";s:13:"Vastu Shastra";s:4:"slug";s:13:"vastu-shastra";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1403";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:377:"Vastu Shastra is an ancient Indian science of architecture that creates flow of energy in a home, office or any other setting. Vastu experts use the knowledge and study of five elements, four directions, nature, magnetic energy fields and gravity to help people streamline and determine how it affects all aspects of their life such as health, wealth, abundance and prosperity.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1391";s:5:"count";s:2:"15";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"15";}i:152;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1412";s:4:"name";s:12:"Vinyasa Yoga";s:4:"slug";s:12:"vinyasa-yoga";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1412";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:297:"Vinyasa Yoga is a gradual step-by-step approach that systematically uses the union of breath and movement to create a ‚Äúflow‚Äù. Vinyasa Yoga creates a flow of movement meditation through a specific sequence of asanas that bring the mind, body and soul of the practitioner to balance and harmony.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1410";s:5:"count";s:2:"44";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"37";}i:153;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1496";s:4:"name";s:20:"Vipassana Meditation";s:4:"slug";s:20:"vipassana-meditation";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1496";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:401:"Vipassana Meditation was rediscovered by Gautama Buddha more than 2500 years ago. In this practice, one goes into complete silence for a minimum of 10 days. Being in this silence takes you within to observe yourself and face your emotions. This conscious awareness and presence dissolves the emotions. In the 10-day Vipassana program there is no speaking and is referred to as the ‚Äònoble silence‚Äô.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1491";s:5:"count";s:2:"31";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"2";}i:154;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1455";s:4:"name";s:22:"Voice Movement Therapy";s:4:"slug";s:22:"voice-movement-therapy";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1455";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:414:"The human voice reflects both physical and psychic states and has the ability to convey cognitive meaning and emotive expression simultaneously. Our voice is our primary mode of communication for both, ideas and feelings and can help us express primal sounds that enable healing. Voice Movement Therapy is used to express emotion through tone which expresses the emotional message underlying what we speak or sing.";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1452";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:1:"2";}i:155;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"2957";s:4:"name";s:14:"Wellness Coach";s:4:"slug";s:14:"wellness-coach";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"2957";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:545:"Wellness coaching is beneficial for people looking to achieve their goals and maintain a healthy lifestyle. Wellness coaches advise their clients on career, relationships, finances and physical health and diet. They help their clients realise their dreams, refocus their agenda on making those dreams come true, recognise obstacles, recommend appropriate solutions and motivate them to play on their strengths and hone their skills. Wellness coaching can boost optimism and productivity, foster a healthy work life balance and lower stress. 

";s:6:"parent";s:4:"1557";s:5:"count";s:2:"48";s:8:"COUNT(*)";s:2:"44";}i:156;O:8:"stdClass":10:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1795";s:4:"name";s:8:"Yin Yoga";s:4:"slug";s:8:"yin-yoga";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1795";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"therapy";s:11:"description";s:504:"
